{
  "texts": [
    "However, these steps, while effective in domains with simple concepts and interactions, prove inefficient in the complex biological domain, with entity relations specific to organisms, cell function, or disease conditions.",
    "In the relation extraction (RE) stage following pre-processing, statistical methods aim to capture entity relationships through feature extraction [1].",
    "Approaches such as sentence simplification [12], link grammar parsing [13], and a combination of vector and tree-based kernels [14] enhance protein-protein interaction (PPI) relation extraction in simpler sentences.",
    "However, these methods face limitations in handling complex biological sentences, and simplification can lead to overfitting and information loss.",
    "These methods heavily depend on tools like MedPost (a POS tagger) or existing biological knowledge bases."
  ]
}